t: Many*p a time have they afflicted me from my youth, may Israel now say:
Many*p a time have they afflicted me from my youth: yet they have not prevailed against me.
The*p plowers plowed upon my back: they made long their furrows.
The*p Lord*s is righteous: he hath cut asunder the cords of the wicked.
Let*p them all be confounded and turned back that hate Zion.
Let*p them be as the grass upon the housetops, which withereth afore it groweth up:
Wherewith*p the mower filleth not his hand; nor he that bindeth sheaves his bosom.
Neither*p do they which go by say, The blessing of the Lord*s be upon you: we bless you in the name of the Lord.*s
